accel_to_decel_enable.description: Klipper's max_accel_to_decel will be adjusted automatically
accel_to_decel_enable.label: Enable accel_to_decel

accel_to_decel_factor.description: Klipper's max_accel_to_decel will be adjusted to this %% of acceleration
accel_to_decel_factor.label: accel_to_decel

acceleration_limit_mess_enable.description: Weight limit speed and acceleration Enable
acceleration_limit_mess_enable.label: Weight limit speed and acceleration Enable

activate_air_filtration.description: Activate for better air filtration. G-code command: M106 P3 S(0-255)
activate_air_filtration.label: Activate air filtration

activate_chamber_temp_control.description:
Enable this option for chamber temperature control. An M191 command will be added before "machine_start_gcode"
G-code commands: M141/M191 S(0-255)
activate_chamber_temp_control.label: Activate temperature control

adaptive_bed_mesh_margin.description: This option determines the additional distance by which the adaptive bed mesh area should be expanded in the XY directions.
adaptive_bed_mesh_margin.label: Mesh margin

enable_special_area_additional_cooling_f.description: Enable special area additional cooling fan.
enable_special_area_additional_cooling_f.label: Enable special area additional cooling fan

additional_cooling_fan_speed.description:
Speed of auxiliary part cooling fan. Auxiliary fan will run at this speed during printing except the first several layers which is defined by no cooling layers.
Please enable auxiliary_fan in printer settings to use this feature. G-code command: M106 P2 S(0-255)
additional_cooling_fan_speed.label: Fan speed

alternate_extra_wall.description:
This setting adds an extra wall to every other layer. This way the infill gets wedged vertically between the walls, resulting in stronger prints. 

When this option is enabled, the ensure vertical shell thickness option needs to be disabled. 

Using lightning infill together with this option is not recommended as there is limited infill to anchor the extra perimeters to.
alternate_extra_wall.label: Alternate extra wall

auxiliary_fan.description: Enable this option if machine has auxiliary part cooling fan. G-code command: M106 P2 S(0-255).
auxiliary_fan.label: Auxiliary part cooling fan

bbl_use_printhost.description: Allow controlling BambuLab's printer through 3rd party print hosts
bbl_use_printhost.label: Use 3rd-party print host

bed_exclude_area.description: Unprintable area in XY plane. For example, X1 Series printers use the front left corner to cut filament during filament change. The area is expressed as polygon by points in following format: "XxY, XxY, ..."
bed_exclude_area.label: Bed exclude area

bed_mesh_max.description: This option sets the max point for the allowed bed mesh area. Due to the probe's XY offset, most printers are unable to probe the entire bed. To ensure the probe point does not go outside the bed area, the minimum and maximum points of the bed mesh should be set appropriately. OrcaSlicer ensures that adaptive_bed_mesh_min/adaptive_bed_mesh_max values do not exceed these min/max points. This information can usually be obtained from your printer manufacturer. The default setting is (99999, 99999), which means there are no limits, thus allowing probing across the entire bed.
bed_mesh_max.label: Bed mesh max

bed_mesh_min.description: This option sets the min point for the allowed bed mesh area. Due to the probe's XY offset, most printers are unable to probe the entire bed. To ensure the probe point does not go outside the bed area, the minimum and maximum points of the bed mesh should be set appropriately. OrcaSlicer ensures that adaptive_bed_mesh_min/adaptive_bed_mesh_max values do not exceed these min/max points. This information can usually be obtained from your printer manufacturer. The default setting is (-99999, -99999), which means there are no limits, thus allowing probing across the entire bed.
bed_mesh_min.label: Bed mesh min

bed_mesh_probe_distance.description: This option sets the preferred distance between probe points (grid size) for the X and Y directions, with the default being 50mm for both X and Y.
bed_mesh_probe_distance.label: Probe point distance

before_layer_change_gcode.description: This G-code is inserted at every layer change before lifting z
before_layer_change_gcode.label: Before layer change G-code

best_object_pos.description: Best auto arranging position in range [0,1] w.r.t. bed shape.
best_object_pos.label: Best object position

bottom_shell_layers.description: This is the number of solid layers of bottom shell, including the bottom surface layer. When the thickness calculated by this value is thinner than bottom shell thickness, the bottom shell layers will be increased
bottom_shell_layers.label: Bottom shell layers

bottom_shell_thickness.description: The number of bottom solid layers is increased when slicing if the thickness calculated by bottom shell layers is thinner than this value. This can avoid having too thin shell when layer height is small. 0 means that this setting is disabled and thickness of bottom shell is absolutely determained by bottom shell layers
bottom_shell_thickness.label: Bottom shell thickness

bottom_solid_infill_flow_ratio.description: This factor affects the amount of material for bottom solid infill
bottom_solid_infill_flow_ratio.label: Bottom surface flow ratio

bottom_surface_pattern.description: Line pattern of bottom surface infill, not bridge infill
bottom_surface_pattern.label: Bottom surface pattern

bridge_acceleration.description: Acceleration of bridges. If the value is expressed as a percentage (e.g. 50%), it will be calculated based on the outer wall acceleration.
bridge_acceleration.label: Bridge

bridge_angle.description: Bridging angle override. If left to zero, the bridging angle will be calculated automatically. Otherwise the provided angle will be used for external bridges. Use 180.for zero angle.
bridge_angle.label: Bridge infill direction

bridge_density.description: Density of external bridges. 100% means solid bridge. Default is 100%.
bridge_density.label: Bridge density

bridge_flow.description: Decrease this value slightly(for example 0.9) to reduce the amount of material for bridge, to improve sag
bridge_flow.label: Bridge flow ratio

bridge_no_support.description: Don't support the whole bridge area which make support very large. Bridge usually can be printing directly without support if not very long
bridge_no_support.label: Don't support bridges

bridge_speed.description: Speed of bridge and completely overhang wall
bridge_speed.label: External

brim_ears.description: Only draw brim over the sharp edges of the model.
brim_ears.label: Brim ears

brim_ears_detection_length.description:
The geometry will be decimated before dectecting sharp angles. This parameter indicates the minimum length of the deviation for the decimation.
0 to deactivate
brim_ears_detection_length.label: Brim ear detection radius

brim_ears_max_angle.description:
Maximum angle to let a brim ear appear. 
If set to 0, no brim will be created. 
If set to ~180, brim will be created on everything but straight sections.
brim_ears_max_angle.label: Brim ear max angle

brim_object_gap.description: A gap between innermost brim line and object can make brim be removed more easily
brim_object_gap.label: Brim-object gap

brim_type.description: This controls the generation of the brim at outer and/or inner side of models. Auto means the brim width is analysed and calculated automatically.
brim_type.label: Brim type

brim_width.description: Distance from model to the outermost brim line
brim_width.label: Brim width

chamber_temperature.description: Higher chamber temperature can help suppress or reduce warping and potentially lead to higher interlayer bonding strength for high temperature materials like ABS, ASA, PC, PA and so on.At the same time, the air filtration of ABS and ASA will get worse.While for PLA, PETG, TPU, PVA and other low temperature materials,the actual chamber temperature should not be high to avoid cloggings, so 0 which stands for turning off is highly recommended
chamber_temperature.label: Chamber temperature

change_extrusion_role_gcode.description: This gcode is inserted when the extrusion role is changed
change_extrusion_role_gcode.label: Change extrusion role G-code

change_filament_gcode.description: This gcode is inserted when change filament, including T command to trigger tool change
change_filament_gcode.label: Change filament G-code

close_fan_the_first_x_layers.description: Close all cooling fan for the first certain layers. Cooling fan of the first layer used to be closed to get better build plate adhesion
close_fan_the_first_x_layers.label: No cooling for the first

complete_print_exhaust_fan_speed.description: Speed of exhuast fan after printing completes
complete_print_exhaust_fan_speed.label: Fan speed

cool_cds_fan_start_at_height.description: The height at which the Cds fans spin on regular fan speed.
cool_cds_fan_start_at_height.label: Regular Cds Fan Speed at Height

cool_plate_temp.description: Bed temperature for layers except the initial one. Value 0 means the filament does not support to print on the Cool Plate
cool_plate_temp.label: Other layers

cool_plate_temp_initial_layer.description: Bed temperature of the initial layer. Value 0 means the filament does not support to print on the Cool Plate
cool_plate_temp_initial_layer.label: Initial layer

epoxy_resin_plate_temp.description: Bed temperature for layers except the initial one. Value 0 means the filament does not support to print on the Epoxy Resin Plate
epoxy_resin_plate_temp.label: Other layers

epoxy_resin_plate_temp_initial_layer.description: Bed temperature of the initial layer. Value 0 means the filament does not support to print on the Epoxy Resin Plate
epoxy_resin_plate_temp_initial_layer.label: Initial layer

cool_special_cds_fan_speed.description:
Speed of auxiliary part cooling fan.Auxiliary fan will run at this speed during printing except the first several layers which is defined by no cooling layers.
Please enable auxiliary_fan in printer settings to use this feature. G-code command: M106 P2 S(0-255)
cool_special_cds_fan_speed.label: Fan speed for overhangs

cooling_tube_length.description: Length of the cooling tube to limit space for cooling moves inside it.
cooling_tube_length.label: Cooling tube length

cooling_tube_retraction.description: Distance of the center-point of the cooling tube from the extruder tip.
cooling_tube_retraction.label: Cooling tube position

counterbore_hole_bridging.description:
This option creates bridges for counterbore holes, allowing them to be printed without support. Available modes include:
1. None: No bridge is created.
2. Partially Bridged: Only a part of the unsupported area will be bridged.
3. Sacrificial Layer: A full sacrificial bridge layer is created.
counterbore_hole_bridging.label: Bridge counterbore holes

curr_bed_type.description: Bed types supported by the printer
curr_bed_type.label: Bed type

options.High Temp Plate: Smooth PEI Plate / High Temp Plate

default_acceleration.description: The default acceleration of both normal printing and travel except initial layer
default_acceleration.label: Normal printing

default_filament_profile.description: Default filament profile when switch to this machine profile
default_filament_profile.label: Default filament profile

default_print_profile.description: Default process profile when switch to this machine profile
default_print_profile.label: Default process profile

deretraction_speed.description: Speed for reloading filament into extruder. Zero means same speed with retraction
deretraction_speed.label: Deretraction Speed

detect_narrow_internal_solid_infill.description: This option will auto detect narrow internal solid infill area. If enabled, concentric pattern will be used for the area to speed printing up. Otherwise, rectilinear pattern is used defaultly.
detect_narrow_internal_solid_infill.label: Detect narrow internal solid infill

detect_overhang_wall.description: Detect the overhang percentage relative to line width and use different speed to print. For 100%% overhang, bridge speed is used.
detect_overhang_wall.label: Detect overhang wall

detect_thin_wall.description: Detect thin wall which can't contain two line width. And use single line to print. Maybe printed not very well, because it's not closed loop
detect_thin_wall.label: Detect thin wall

disable_m73.description: Disable generating of the M73: Set remaining print time in the final gcode
disable_m73.label: Disable set remaining print time

dont_filter_internal_bridges.description:
This option can help reducing pillowing on top surfaces in heavily slanted or curved models.

By default, small internal bridges are filtered out and the internal solid infill is printed directly over the sparse infill. This works well in most cases, speeding up printing without too much compromise on top surface quality. 

However, in heavily slanted or curved models especially where too low sparse infill density is used, this may result in curling of the unsupported solid infill, causing pillowing.

Enabling this option will print internal bridge layer over slightly unsupported internal solid infill. The options below control the amount of filtering, i.e. the amount of internal bridges created.

Disabled - Disables this option. This is the default behaviour and works well in most cases.

Limited filtering - Creates internal bridges on heavily slanted surfaces, while avoiding creating uncessesary interal bridges. This works well for most difficult models.

No filtering - Creates internal bridges on every potential internal overhang. This option is useful for heavily slanted top surface models. However, in most cases it creates too many unecessary bridges.
dont_filter_internal_bridges.label: Don't filter out small internal bridges (beta)

during_print_exhaust_fan_speed.description: Speed of exhuast fan during printing.This speed will overwrite the speed in filament custom gcode
during_print_exhaust_fan_speed.label: Fan speed

elefant_foot_compensation.description: Shrink the initial layer on build plate to compensate for elephant foot effect
elefant_foot_compensation.label: Elephant foot compensation

elefant_foot_compensation_layers.description: The number of layers on which the elephant foot compensation will be active. The first layer will be shrunk by the elephant foot compensation value, then the next layers will be linearly shrunk less, up to the layer indicated by this value.
elefant_foot_compensation_layers.label: Elephant foot compensation layers

emit_machine_limits_to_gcode.description:
If enabled, the machine limits will be emitted to G-code file.
This option will be ignored if the g-code flavor is set to Klipper.
emit_machine_limits_to_gcode.label: Emit limits to G-code

enable_arc_fitting.description: Enable this to get a G-code file which has G2 and G3 moves. And the fitting tolerance is same with resolution
enable_arc_fitting.label: Arc fitting

enable_overhang_bridge_fan.description: Enable this option to optimize part cooling fan speed for overhang and bridge to get better cooling
enable_overhang_bridge_fan.label: Force cooling for overhang and bridge

enable_overhang_speed.description: Enable this option to slow printing down for different overhang degree
enable_overhang_speed.label: Slow down for overhang

enable_pressure_advance.description: Enable pressure advance, auto calibration result will be overwriten once enabled.
enable_pressure_advance.label: Enable pressure advance

enable_prime_tower.description: The wiping tower can be used to clean up the residue on the nozzle and stabilize the chamber pressure inside the nozzle, in order to avoid appearance defects when printing objects.
enable_prime_tower.label: Enable

eng_plate_temp.description: Bed temperature for layers except the initial one. Value 0 means the filament does not support to print on the Engineering Plate
eng_plate_temp.label: Other layers

eng_plate_temp_initial_layer.description: Bed temperature of the initial layer. Value 0 means the filament does not support to print on the Engineering Plate
eng_plate_temp_initial_layer.label: Initial layer

ensure_vertical_shell_thickness.description:
Add solid infill near sloping surfaces to guarantee the vertical shell thickness (top+bottom solid layers)
None: No solid infill will be added anywhere. Caution: Use this option carefully if your model has sloped surfaces
Critical Only: Avoid adding solid infill for walls
Moderate: Add solid infill for heavily sloping surfaces only
All: Add solid infill for all suitable sloping surfaces
Default value is All.
ensure_vertical_shell_thickness.label: Ensure vertical shell thickness

exclude_object.description: Enable this option to add EXCLUDE OBJECT command in g-code
exclude_object.label: Exclude objects

extra_loading_move.description: When set to zero, the distance the filament is moved from parking position during load is exactly the same as it was moved back during unload. When positive, it is loaded further,  if negative, the loading move is shorter than unloading.
extra_loading_move.label: Extra loading distance

extra_perimeters_on_overhangs.description: Create additional perimeter paths over steep overhangs and areas where bridges cannot be anchored.
extra_perimeters_on_overhangs.label: Extra perimeters on overhangs

extruder_clearance_height_to_lid.description: Distance of the nozzle tip to the lid. Used for collision avoidance in by-object printing.
extruder_clearance_height_to_lid.label: Height to lid

extruder_clearance_height_to_rod.description: Distance of the nozzle tip to the lower rod. Used for collision avoidance in by-object printing.
extruder_clearance_height_to_rod.label: Height to rod

extruder_clearance_radius.description: Clearance radius around extruder. Used for collision avoidance in by-object printing.
extruder_clearance_radius.label: Radius

extruder_colour.description: Only used as a visual help on UI
extruder_colour.label: Extruder Color

fan_cooling_layer_time.description: Part cooling fan will be enabled for layers of which estimated time is shorter than this value. Fan speed is interpolated between the minimum and maximum fan speeds according to layer printing time
fan_cooling_layer_time.label: Layer time

fan_kickstart.description:
Emit a max fan speed command for this amount of seconds before reducing to target speed to kick-start the cooling fan.
This is useful for fans where a low PWM/power may be insufficient to get the fan started spinning from a stop, or to get the fan up to speed faster.
Set to 0 to deactivate.
fan_kickstart.label: Fan kick-start time

fan_max_speed.description: Part cooling fan speed may be increased when auto cooling is enabled. This is the maximum speed limitation of part cooling fan
fan_max_speed.label: Fan speed

fan_min_speed.description: Minimum speed for part cooling fan
fan_min_speed.label: Fan speed

fan_speedup_overhangs.description: Will only take into account the delay for the cooling of overhangs.
fan_speedup_overhangs.label: Only overhangs

fan_speedup_time.description:
Start the fan this number of seconds earlier than its target start time (you can use fractional seconds). It assumes infinite acceleration for this time estimation, and will only take into account G1 and G0 moves (arc fitting is unsupported).
It won't move fan comands from custom gcodes (they act as a sort of 'barrier').
It won't move fan comands into the start gcode if the 'only custom start gcode' is activated.
Use 0 to deactivate.
fan_speedup_time.label: Fan speed-up time

filament_colour.description: Only used as a visual help on UI
filament_colour.label: Color

filament_cooling_final_speed.description: Cooling moves are gradually accelerating towards this speed.
filament_cooling_final_speed.label: Speed of the last cooling move

filament_cooling_initial_speed.description: Cooling moves are gradually accelerating beginning at this speed.
filament_cooling_initial_speed.label: Speed of the first cooling move

filament_cooling_moves.description: Filament is cooled by being moved back and forth in the cooling tubes. Specify desired number of these moves.
filament_cooling_moves.label: Number of cooling moves

filament_deretraction_speed.description: Speed for reloading filament into extruder. Zero means same speed with retraction
filament_deretraction_speed.label: Deretraction Speed

filament_diameter.description: Filament diameter is used to calculate extrusion in gcode, so it's important and should be accurate
filament_diameter.label: Diameter

filament_end_gcode.description: End G-code when finish the printing of this filament
filament_end_gcode.label: End G-code

filament_flow_ratio.description: The material may have volumetric change after switching between molten state and crystalline state. This setting changes all extrusion flow of this filament in gcode proportionally. Recommended value range is between 0.95 and 1.05. Maybe you can tune this value to get nice flat surface when there has slight overflow or underflow
filament_flow_ratio.label: Flow ratio

filament_is_support.description: Support material is commonly used to print support and support interface
filament_is_support.label: Support material

filament_load_time.description: Time for the printer firmware (or the Multi Material Unit 2.0) to load a new filament during a tool change (when executing the T code). This time is added to the total print time by the G-code time estimator.
filament_load_time.label: Filament load time

filament_loading_speed.description: Speed used for loading the filament on the wipe tower.
filament_loading_speed.label: Loading speed

filament_loading_speed_start.description: Speed used at the very beginning of loading phase.
filament_loading_speed_start.label: Loading speed at the start

filament_max_volumetric_speed.description: This setting stands for how much volume of filament can be melted and extruded per second. Printing speed is limited by max volumetric speed, in case of too high and unreasonable speed setting. Can't be zero
filament_max_volumetric_speed.label: Max volumetric speed

filament_minimal_purge_on_wipe_tower.description: After a tool change, the exact position of the newly loaded filament inside the nozzle may not be known, and the filament pressure is likely not yet stable. Before purging the print head into an infill or a sacrificial object, Orca Slicer will always prime this amount of material into the wipe tower to produce successive infill or sacrificial object extrusions reliably.
filament_minimal_purge_on_wipe_tower.label: Minimal purge on wipe tower

filament_multitool_ramming.description: Perform ramming when using multitool printer (i.e. when the 'Single Extruder Multimaterial' in Printer Settings is unchecked). When checked, a small amount of filament is rapidly extruded on the wipe tower just before the toolchange. This option is only used when the wipe tower is enabled.
filament_multitool_ramming.label: Enable ramming for multitool setups

filament_multitool_ramming_flow.description: Flow used for ramming the filament before the toolchange.
filament_multitool_ramming_flow.label: Multitool ramming flow

filament_multitool_ramming_volume.description: The volume to be rammed before the toolchange.
filament_multitool_ramming_volume.label: Multitool ramming volume

filament_notes.description: You can put your notes regarding the filament here.
filament_notes.label: Filament notes

filament_ramming_parameters.description: This string is edited by RammingDialog and contains ramming specific parameters.
filament_ramming_parameters.label: Ramming parameters

filament_retract_before_wipe.description: The length of fast retraction before wipe, relative to retraction length
filament_retract_before_wipe.label: Retract amount before wipe

filament_retract_lift_above.description: If you set this to a positive value, Z lift will only take place above the specified absolute Z.
filament_retract_lift_above.label: Only lift Z above

filament_retract_lift_below.description: If you set this to a positive value, Z lift will only take place below the specified absolute Z.
filament_retract_lift_below.label: Only lift Z below

filament_retract_lift_enforce.description: Enforce Z Hop behavior. This setting is impacted by the above settings (Only lift Z above/below).
filament_retract_lift_enforce.label: On surfaces

filament_retract_restart_extra.description: When the retraction is compensated after the travel move, the extruder will push this additional amount of filament. This setting is rarely needed.
filament_retract_restart_extra.label: Extra length on restart

filament_retract_when_changing_layer.description: Force a retraction when changes layer
filament_retract_when_changing_layer.label: Retract when change layer

filament_retraction_length.description: Some amount of material in extruder is pulled back to avoid ooze during long travel. Set zero to disable retraction
filament_retraction_length.label: Length

filament_retraction_minimum_travel.description: Only trigger retraction when the travel distance is longer than this threshold
filament_retraction_minimum_travel.label: Travel distance threshold

filament_shrink.description:
Enter the shrinkage percentage that the filament will get after cooling (94% if you measure 94mm instead of 100mm). The part will be scaled in xy to compensate. Only the filament used for the perimeter is taken into account.
Be sure to allow enough space between objects, as this compensation is done after the checks.
filament_shrink.label: Shrinkage

filament_soluble.description: Soluble material is commonly used to print support and support interface
filament_soluble.label: Soluble material

filament_start_gcode.description: Start G-code when start the printing of this filament
filament_start_gcode.label: Start G-code

filament_toolchange_delay.description: Time to wait after the filament is unloaded. May help to get reliable toolchanges with flexible materials that may need more time to shrink to original dimensions.
filament_toolchange_delay.label: Delay after unloading

filament_unload_time.description: Time for the printer firmware (or the Multi Material Unit 2.0) to unload a filament during a tool change (when executing the T code). This time is added to the total print time by the G-code time estimator.
filament_unload_time.label: Filament unload time

filament_unloading_speed.description: Speed used for unloading the filament on the wipe tower (does not affect  initial part of unloading just after ramming).
filament_unloading_speed.label: Unloading speed

filament_unloading_speed_start.description: Speed used for unloading the tip of the filament immediately after ramming.
filament_unloading_speed_start.label: Unloading speed at the start

filament_vendor.description: Vendor of filament. For show only
filament_vendor.label: Vendor

filament_wipe.description: Move nozzle along the last extrusion path when retracting to clean leaked material on nozzle. This can minimize blob when print new part after travel
filament_wipe.label: Wipe while retracting

filament_wipe_distance.description:
Discribe how long the nozzle will move along the last path when retracting. 

Depending on how long the wipe operation lasts, how fast and long the extruder/filament retraction settings are, a retraction move may be needed to retract the remaining filament. 

Setting a value in the retract amount before wipe setting below will perform any excess retraction before the wipe, else it will be performed after.
filament_wipe_distance.label: Wipe Distance

filament_z_hop.description: Whenever the retraction is done, the nozzle is lifted a little to create clearance between nozzle and the print. It prevents nozzle from hitting the print when travel move. Using spiral line to lift z can prevent stringing
filament_z_hop.label: Z hop when retract

filename_format.description: User can self-define the project file name when export
filename_format.label: Filename format

filter_out_gap_fill.description: Filter out gaps smaller than the threshold specified
filter_out_gap_fill.label: Filter out tiny gaps

flush_into_infill.description: Purging after filament change will be done inside objects' infills. This may lower the amount of waste and decrease the print time. If the walls are printed with transparent filament, the mixed color infill will be seen outside. It will not take effect, unless the prime tower is enabled.
flush_into_infill.label: Flush into objects' infill

flush_into_objects.description: This object will be used to purge the nozzle after a filament change to save filament and decrease the print time. Colours of the objects will be mixed as a result. It will not take effect, unless the prime tower is enabled.
flush_into_objects.label: Flush into this object

flush_into_support.description: Purging after filament change will be done inside objects' support. This may lower the amount of waste and decrease the print time. It will not take effect, unless the prime tower is enabled.
flush_into_support.label: Flush into objects' support

flush_multiplier.description: The actual flushing volumes is equal to the flush multiplier multiplied by the flushing volumes in the table.
flush_multiplier.label: Flush multiplier

creality_flush_time.description: The flushing time during color change
creality_flush_time.label: The flushing time during color change

full_fan_speed_layer.description: Fan speed will be ramped up linearly from zero at layer "close_fan_the_first_x_layers" to maximum at layer "full_fan_speed_layer". "full_fan_speed_layer" will be ignored if lower than "close_fan_the_first_x_layers", in which case the fan will be running at maximum allowed speed at layer "close_fan_the_first_x_layers" + 1.
full_fan_speed_layer.label: Full fan speed at layer

fuzzy_skin.description: Randomly jitter while printing the wall, so that the surface has a rough look. This setting controls the fuzzy position
fuzzy_skin.label: Fuzzy Skin

fuzzy_skin_first_layer.description: Whether to apply fuzzy skin on the first layer
fuzzy_skin_first_layer.label: Apply fuzzy skin to first layer

fuzzy_skin_point_distance.description: The average diatance between the random points introducded on each line segment
fuzzy_skin_point_distance.label: Fuzzy skin point distance

fuzzy_skin_thickness.description: The width within which to jitter. It's adversed to be below outer wall line width
fuzzy_skin_thickness.label: Fuzzy skin thickness

gap_fill_target.description:
Enables gap fill for the selected surfaces. The minimum gap length that will be filled can be controlled from the filter out tiny gaps option below.

Options:
1. Everywhere: Applies gap fill to top, bottom and internal solid surfaces
2. Top and Bottom surfaces: Applies gap fill to top and bottom surfaces only
3. Nowhere: Disables gap fill
gap_fill_target.label: Apply gap fill

gap_infill_speed.description: Speed of gap infill. Gap usually has irregular line width and should be printed more slowly
gap_infill_speed.label: Gap infill

gcode_add_line_number.description: Enable this to add line number(Nx) at the beginning of each G-Code line
gcode_add_line_number.label: Add line number

gcode_comments.description: Enable this to get a commented G-code file, with each line explained by a descriptive text. If you print from SD card, the additional weight of the file could make your firmware slow down.
gcode_comments.label: Verbose G-code

gcode_flavor.description: What kind of gcode the printer is compatible with
gcode_flavor.label: G-code flavor

gcode_label_objects.description: Enable this to add comments into the G-Code labeling print moves with what object they belong to, which is useful for the Octoprint CancelObject plugin. This settings is NOT compatible with Single Extruder Multi Material setup and Wipe into Object / Wipe into Infill.
gcode_label_objects.label: Label objects

high_current_on_filament_swap.description: It may be beneficial to increase the extruder motor current during the filament exchange sequence to allow for rapid ramming feed rates and to overcome resistance when loading a filament with an ugly shaped tip.
high_current_on_filament_swap.label: High extruder current on filament swap

hole_to_polyhole.description:
Search for almost-circular holes that span more than one layer and convert the geometry to polyholes. Use the nozzle size and the (biggest) diameter to compute the polyhole.
See http://hydraraptor.blogspot.com/2011/02/polyholes.html
hole_to_polyhole.label: Convert holes to polyholes

hole_to_polyhole_threshold.description:
Maximum defection of a point to the estimated radius of the circle.
As cylinders are often exported as triangles of varying size, points may not be on the circle circumference. This setting allows you some leway to broaden the detection.
In mm or in % of the radius.
hole_to_polyhole_threshold.label: Polyhole detection margin

host_type.description: Orca Slicer can upload G-code files to a printer host. This field must contain the kind of the host.
host_type.label: Host Type

hot_plate_temp.description: Bed temperature for layers except the initial one. Value 0 means the filament does not support to print on the High Temp Plate
hot_plate_temp.label: Other layers

hot_plate_temp_initial_layer.description: Bed temperature of the initial layer. Value 0 means the filament does not support to print on the High Temp Plate
hot_plate_temp_initial_layer.label: Initial layer

independent_support_layer_height.description: Support layer uses layer height independent with object layer. This is to support customizing z-gap and save print time.This option will be invalid when the prime tower is enabled.
independent_support_layer_height.label: Independent support layer height

infill_anchor.description:
Connect an infill line to an internal perimeter with a short segment of an additional perimeter. If expressed as percentage (example: 15%) it is calculated over infill extrusion width. Orca Slicer tries to connect two close infill lines to a short perimeter segment. If no such perimeter segment shorter than infill_anchor_max is found, the infill line is connected to a perimeter segment at just one side and the length of the perimeter segment taken is limited to this parameter, but no longer than anchor_length_max. 
Set this parameter to zero to disable anchoring perimeters connected to a single infill line.
infill_anchor.label: Sparse infill anchor length

infill_anchor_max.description:
Connect an infill line to an internal perimeter with a short segment of an additional perimeter. If expressed as percentage (example: 15%) it is calculated over infill extrusion width. Orca Slicer tries to connect two close infill lines to a short perimeter segment. If no such perimeter segment shorter than this parameter is found, the infill line is connected to a perimeter segment at just one side and the length of the perimeter segment taken is limited to infill_anchor, but no longer than this parameter. 
If set to 0, the old algorithm for infill connection will be used, it should create the same result as with 1000 & 0.
infill_anchor_max.label: Maximum length of the infill anchor

infill_combination.description: Automatically Combine sparse infill of several layers to print together to reduce time. Wall is still printed with original layer height.
infill_combination.label: Infill combination

infill_direction.description: Angle for sparse infill pattern, which controls the start or main direction of line
infill_direction.label: Infill direction

infill_wall_overlap.description: Infill area is enlarged slightly to overlap with wall for better bonding. The percentage value is relative to line width of sparse infill
infill_wall_overlap.label: Infill/Wall overlap

initial_layer_acceleration.description: Acceleration of initial layer. Using a lower value can improve build plate adhesive
initial_layer_acceleration.label: Initial layer

initial_layer_infill_speed.description: Speed of solid infill part of initial layer
initial_layer_infill_speed.label: Initial layer infill

initial_layer_line_width.description: Line width of initial layer. If expressed as a %, it will be computed over the nozzle diameter.
initial_layer_line_width.label: Initial layer

initial_layer_min_bead_width.description: The minimum wall width that should be used for the first layer is recommended to be set to the same size as the nozzle. This adjustment is expected to enhance adhesion.
initial_layer_min_bead_width.label: First layer minimum wall width

initial_layer_print_height.description: Height of initial layer. Making initial layer height to be thick slightly can improve build plate adhension
initial_layer_print_height.label: Initial layer height

initial_layer_speed.description: Speed of initial layer except the solid infill part
initial_layer_speed.label: Initial layer

inner_wall_line_width.description: Line width of inner wall. If expressed as a %, it will be computed over the nozzle diameter.
inner_wall_line_width.label: Inner wall

interface_shells.description: Force the generation of solid shells between adjacent materials/volumes. Useful for multi-extruder prints with translucent materials or manual soluble support material
interface_shells.label: Interface shells

internal_bridge_flow.description: This value governs the thickness of the internal bridge layer. This is the first layer over sparse infill. Decrease this value slightly (for example 0.9) to improve surface quality over sparse infill.
internal_bridge_flow.label: Internal bridge flow ratio

internal_bridge_speed.description: Speed of internal bridge. If the value is expressed as a percentage, it will be calculated based on the bridge_speed. Default value is 150%.
internal_bridge_speed.label: Internal

internal_solid_infill_acceleration.description: Acceleration of internal solid infill. If the value is expressed as a percentage (e.g. 100%), it will be calculated based on the default acceleration.
internal_solid_infill_acceleration.label: Internal solid infill

internal_solid_infill_line_width.description: Line width of internal solid infill. If expressed as a %, it will be computed over the nozzle diameter.
internal_solid_infill_line_width.label: Internal solid infill

internal_solid_infill_pattern.description: Line pattern of internal solid infill. if the detect narrow internal solid infill be enabled, the concentric pattern will be used for the small area.
internal_solid_infill_pattern.label: Internal solid infill pattern

internal_solid_infill_speed.description: Speed of internal solid infill, not the top and bottom surface
internal_solid_infill_speed.label: Internal solid infill

ironing_angle.description: The angle ironing is done at. A negative number disables this function and uses the default method.
ironing_angle.label: Ironing angle

ironing_flow.description: The amount of material to extrude during ironing. Relative to flow of normal layer height. Too high value results in overextrusion on the surface
ironing_flow.label: Ironing flow

ironing_pattern.description: The pattern that will be used when ironing
ironing_pattern.label: Ironing Pattern

ironing_spacing.description: The distance between the lines of ironing
ironing_spacing.label: Ironing line spacing

ironing_type.description: Ironing is using small flow to print on same height of surface again to make flat surface more smooth. This setting controls which layer being ironed
ironing_type.label: Ironing Type

is_infill_first.description:
Order of wall/infill. When the tickbox is unchecked the walls are printed first, which works best in most cases.

Printing walls first may help with extreme overhangs as the walls have the neighbouring infill to adhere to. However, the infill will slighly push out the printed walls where it is attached to them, resulting in a worse external surface finish. It can also cause the infill to shine through the external surfaces of the part.
is_infill_first.label: Print infill first

layer_change_gcode.label: Layer change G-code

layer_height.description: Slicing height for each layer. Smaller layer height means more accurate and more printing time
layer_height.label: Layer height

line_width.description: Default line width if other line widths are set to 0. If expressed as a %, it will be computed over the nozzle diameter.
line_width.label: Default
