machine_max_acceleration_e.description: Maximum acceleration of the E axis
machine_max_acceleration_e.label: Maximum acceleration E

machine_max_acceleration_travel.description: Maximum acceleration for travel (M204 T), it only applies to Marlin 2
machine_max_acceleration_travel.label: Maximum acceleration for travel

machine_max_acceleration_x.description: Maximum acceleration of the X axis
machine_max_acceleration_x.label: Maximum acceleration X

machine_max_acceleration_y.description: Maximum acceleration of the Y axis
machine_max_acceleration_y.label: Maximum acceleration Y

machine_max_acceleration_z.description: Maximum acceleration of the Z axis
machine_max_acceleration_z.label: Maximum acceleration Z

machine_max_jerk_e.description: Maximum jerk of the E axis
machine_max_jerk_e.label: Maximum jerk E

machine_max_jerk_x.description: Maximum jerk of the X axis
machine_max_jerk_x.label: Maximum jerk X

machine_max_jerk_y.description: Maximum jerk of the Y axis
machine_max_jerk_y.label: Maximum jerk Y

machine_max_jerk_z.description: Maximum jerk of the Z axis
machine_max_jerk_z.label: Maximum jerk Z

machine_pause_gcode.description: This G-code will be used as a code for the pause print. User can insert pause G-code in gcode viewer
machine_pause_gcode.label: Pause G-code

machine_start_gcode.default_value: G28 ; home all axes\nG1 Z5 F5000 ; lift nozzle\n
machine_start_gcode.description: Start G-code when start the whole printing
machine_start_gcode.label: Start G-code

machine_unload_filament_time.description: Time to unload old filament when switch filament. For statistics only
machine_unload_filament_time.label: Filament unload time

make_overhang_printable.description: Modify the geometry to print overhangs without support material.
make_overhang_printable.label: Make overhangs printable

make_overhang_printable_angle.description: Maximum angle of overhangs to allow after making more steep overhangs printable.90. will not change the model at all and allow any overhang, while 0 will replace all overhangs with conical material.
make_overhang_printable_angle.label: Make overhangs printable - Maximum angle

make_overhang_printable_hole_size.description: Maximum area of a hole in the base of the model before it's filled by conical material.A value of 0 will fill all the holes in the model base.
make_overhang_printable_hole_size.label: Make overhangs printable - Hole area

manual_filament_change.description: Enable this option to omit the custom Change filament G-code only at the beginning of the print. The tool change command (e.g., T0) will be skipped throughout the entire print. This is useful for manual multi-material printing, where we use M600/PAUSE to trigger the manual filament change action.
manual_filament_change.label: Manual Filament Change

material_flow_dependent_temperature.description: Change the temperature for each layer automatically with the average flow speed of that layer.
material_flow_dependent_temperature.label: Change the temperature for each layer automatically with the average flow speed of that layer.

material_flow_temp_graph.description: Correspondence between flow rate (mm2/s) and printing temperature (.C).
material_flow_temp_graph.label: Flow Temperature Graph

max_bridge_length.description: Max length of bridges that don't need support. Set it to 0 if you want all bridges to be supported, and set it to a very large value if you don't want any bridges to be supported.
max_bridge_length.label: Max bridge length

max_layer_height.description: The largest printable layer height for extruder. Used tp limits the maximum layer hight when enable adaptive layer height
max_layer_height.label: Max

max_travel_detour_distance.description: Maximum detour distance for avoiding crossing wall. Don't detour if the detour distance is large than this value. Detour length could be specified either as an absolute value or as percentage (for example 50%) of a direct travel path. Zero to disable
max_travel_detour_distance.label: Avoid crossing wall - Max detour length

max_volumetric_extrusion_rate_slope.description:
This parameter smooths out sudden extrusion rate changes that happen when the printer transitions from printing a high flow (high speed/larger width) extrusion to a lower flow (lower speed/smaller width) extrusion and vice versa.

It defines the maximum rate by which the extruded volumetric flow in mm3/sec can change over time. Higher values mean higher extrusion rate changes are allowed, resulting in faster speed transitions.

A value of 0 disables the feature. 

For a high speed, high flow direct drive printer (like the Bambu lab or Voron) this value is usually not needed. However it can provide some marginal benefit in certain cases where feature speeds vary greatly. For example, when there are aggressive slowdowns due to overhangs. In these cases a high value of around 300-350mm3/s2 is recommended as this allows for just enough smoothing to assist pressure advance achieve a smoother flow transition.

For slower printers without pressure advance, the value should be set much lower. A value of 10-15mm3/s2 is a good starting point for direct drive extruders and 5-10mm3/s2 for Bowden style. 

This feature is known as Pressure Equalizer in Prusa slicer.

Note: this parameter disables arc fitting.
max_volumetric_extrusion_rate_slope.label: Extrusion rate smoothing

max_volumetric_extrusion_rate_slope_segm.description:
A lower value results in smoother extrusion rate transitions. However, this results in a significantly larger gcode file and more instructions for the printer to process. 

Default value of 3 works well for most cases. If your printer is stuttering, increase this value to reduce the number of adjustments made

Allowed values: 1-5
max_volumetric_extrusion_rate_slope_segm.label: Smoothing segment length

min_bead_width.description: Width of the wall that will replace thin features (according to the Minimum feature size) of the model. If the Minimum wall width is thinner than the thickness of the feature, the wall will become as thick as the feature itself. It's expressed as a percentage over nozzle diameter
min_bead_width.label: Minimum wall width

min_feature_size.description: Minimum thickness of thin features. Model features that are thinner than this value will not be printed, while features thicker than the Minimum feature size will be widened to the Minimum wall width. It's expressed as a percentage over nozzle diameter
min_feature_size.label: Minimum feature size

min_layer_height.description: The lowest printable layer height for extruder. Used tp limits the minimum layer hight when enable adaptive layer height
min_layer_height.label: Min

min_length_factor.description:
Adjust this value to prevent short, unclosed walls from being printed, which could increase print time. Higher values remove more and longer walls.

NOTE: Bottom and top surfaces will not be affected by this value to prevent visual gaps on the ouside of the model. Adjust 'One wall threshold' in the Advanced settings below to adjust the sensitivity of what is considered a top-surface. 'One wall threshold' is only visibile if this setting is set above the default value of 0.5, or if single-wall top surfaces is enabled.
min_length_factor.label: Minimum wall length

min_width_top_surface.description:
If a top surface has to be printed and it's partially covered by another layer, it won't be considered at a top layer where its width is below this value. This can be useful to not let the 'one perimeter on top' trigger on surface that should be covered only by perimeters. This value can be a mm or a % of the perimeter extrusion width.
Warning: If enabled, artifacts can be created is you have some thin features on the next layer, like letters. Set this setting to 0 to remove these artifacts.
min_width_top_surface.label: One wall threshold

minimum_sparse_infill_area.description: Sparse infill area which is smaller than threshold value is replaced by internal solid infill
minimum_sparse_infill_area.label: Minimum sparse infill threshold

mmu_segmented_region_interlocking_depth.description: Interlocking depth of a segmented region. Zero disables this feature.
mmu_segmented_region_interlocking_depth.label: Interlocking depth of a segmented region

mmu_segmented_region_max_width.description: Maximum width of a segmented region. Zero disables this feature.
mmu_segmented_region_max_width.label: Maximum width of a segmented region

notes.description: You can put here your personal notes. This text will be added to the G-code header comments.
notes.label: Configuration notes

nozzle_hrc.description: The nozzle's hardness. Zero means no checking for nozzle's hardness during slicing.
nozzle_hrc.label: Nozzle HRC

nozzle_temperature.description: Nozzle temperature for layers after the initial one
nozzle_temperature.label: Other layers

nozzle_temperature_initial_layer.description: Nozzle temperature to print initial layer when using this filament
nozzle_temperature_initial_layer.label: Initial layer

nozzle_type.description: The metallic material of nozzle. This determines the abrasive resistance of nozzle, and what kind of filament can be printed
nozzle_type.label: Nozzle type

nozzle_volume.description: Volume of nozzle between the cutter and the end of nozzle
nozzle_volume.label: Nozzle volume

only_one_wall_first_layer.description: Use only one wall on first layer, to give more space to the bottom infill pattern
only_one_wall_first_layer.label: Only one wall on first layer

only_one_wall_top.description: Use only one wall on flat top surface, to give more space to the top infill pattern
only_one_wall_top.label: Only one wall on top surfaces

outer_wall_acceleration.description: Acceleration of outer wall. Using a lower value can improve quality
outer_wall_acceleration.label: Outer wall

outer_wall_line_width.description: Line width of outer wall. If expressed as a %, it will be computed over the nozzle diameter.
outer_wall_line_width.label: Outer wall

outer_wall_speed.description: Speed of outer wall which is outermost and visible. It's used to be slower than inner wall speed to get better quality.
outer_wall_speed.label: Outer wall

overhang_fan_speed.description: Force part cooling fan to be this speed when printing bridge or overhang wall which has large overhang degree. Forcing cooling for overhang and bridge can get better quality for these part
overhang_fan_speed.label: Fan speed for overhang

overhang_fan_threshold.description: Force cooling fan to be specific speed when overhang degree of printed part exceeds this value. Expressed as percentage which indicides how much width of the line without support from lower layer. 0% means forcing cooling for all outer wall no matter how much overhang degree
overhang_fan_threshold.label: Cooling overhang threshold

overhang_reverse.description:
Extrude perimeters that have a part over an overhang in the reverse direction on odd layers. This alternating pattern can drastically improve steep overhangs.

This setting can also help reduce part warping due to the reduction of stresses in the part walls.
overhang_reverse.label: Reverse on odd

overhang_reverse_internal_only.description:
Apply the reverse perimeters logic only on internal perimeters. 

This setting greatly reduces part stresses as they are now distributed in alternating directions. This should reduce part warping while also maintaining external wall quality. This feature can be very useful for warp prone material, like ABS/ASA, and also for elastic filaments, like TPU and Silk PLA. It can also help reduce warping on floating regions over supports.

For this setting to be the most effective, it is recomended to set the Reverse Threshold to 0 so that all internal walls print in alternating directions on odd layers irrespective of their overhang degree.
overhang_reverse_internal_only.label: Reverse only internal perimeters

overhang_reverse_threshold.description:
Number of mm the overhang need to be for the reversal to be considered useful. Can be a % of the perimeter width.
Value 0 enables reversal on every odd layers regardless.
overhang_reverse_threshold.label: Reverse threshold

overhang_speed_classic.description: Enable this option to use classic mode
overhang_speed_classic.label: Classic mode

parking_pos_retraction.description: Distance of the extruder tip from the position where the filament is parked when unloaded. This should match the value in printer firmware.
parking_pos_retraction.label: Filament parking position

post_process.description: If you want to process the output G-code through custom scripts, just list their absolute paths here. Separate multiple scripts with a semicolon. Scripts will be passed the absolute path to the G-code file as the first argument, and they can access the Orca Slicer config settings by reading environment variables.
post_process.label: Post-processing Scripts

precise_outer_wall.description: Improve shell precision by adjusting outer wall spacing. This also improves layer consistency.
precise_outer_wall.label: Precise wall(experimental)

preferred_orientation.description: Automatically orient stls on the Z-axis upon initial import
preferred_orientation.label: Preferred orientation

preset_names.description: Names of presets related to the physical printer
preset_names.label: Printer preset names

pressure_advance.description: Pressure advance(Klipper) AKA Linear advance factor(Marlin)
pressure_advance.label: Pressure advance

prime_volume.description: The volume of material to prime extruder on tower.
prime_volume.label: Prime volume

print_flow_ratio.description: The material may have volumetric change after switching between molten state and crystalline state. This setting changes all extrusion flow of this filament in gcode proportionally. Recommended value range is between 0.95 and 1.05. Maybe you can tune this value to get nice flat surface when there has slight overflow or underflow
print_flow_ratio.label: Flow ratio

print_host.description: Orca Slicer can upload G-code files to a printer host. This field should contain the hostname, IP address or URL of the printer host instance. Print host behind HAProxy with basic auth enabled can be accessed by putting the user name and password into the URL in the following format: https://username:password@your-octopi-address/
print_host.label: Hostname, IP or URL

print_host_webui.description: Specify the URL of your device user interface if it's not same as print_host
print_host_webui.label: Device UI

print_order.description: Print order within a single layer
print_order.label: Intra-layer order

print_sequence.description: Print sequence, layer by layer or object by object
print_sequence.label: Print sequence

printable_height.description: Maximum printable height which is limited by mechanism of printer
printable_height.label: Printable height

printer_notes.description: You can put your notes regarding the printer here.
printer_notes.label: Printer notes

printer_structure.description: The physical arrangement and components of a printing device
printer_structure.label: Printer structure

printhost_apikey.description: Orca Slicer can upload G-code files to a printer host. This field should contain the API Key or the password required for authentication.
printhost_apikey.label: API Key / Password

printhost_cafile.description: Custom CA certificate file can be specified for HTTPS OctoPrint connections, in crt/pem format. If left blank, the default OS CA certificate repository is used.
printhost_cafile.label: HTTPS CA File

printhost_ssl_ignore_revoke.description: Ignore HTTPS certificate revocation checks in case of missing or offline distribution points. One may want to enable this option for self signed certificates if connection fails.
printhost_ssl_ignore_revoke.label: Ignore HTTPS certificate revocation checks

printing_by_object_gcode.description: Insert Gcode between objects. This parameter will only come into effect when you print your models object by object
printing_by_object_gcode.label: Between Object Gcode

purge_in_prime_tower.description: Purge remaining filament into prime tower
purge_in_prime_tower.label: Purge in prime tower

raft_contact_distance.description: Z gap between object and raft. Ignored for soluble interface
raft_contact_distance.label: Raft contact Z distance

raft_expansion.description: Expand all raft layers in XY plane
raft_expansion.label: Raft expansion

raft_first_layer_density.description: Density of the first raft or support layer
raft_first_layer_density.label: Initial layer density

raft_first_layer_expansion.description: Expand the first raft or support layer to improve bed plate adhesion
raft_first_layer_expansion.label: Initial layer expansion

raft_layers.description: Object will be raised by this number of support layers. Use this function to avoid wrapping when print ABS
raft_layers.label: Raft layers

reduce_crossing_wall.description: Detour and avoid to travel across wall which may cause blob on surface
reduce_crossing_wall.label: Avoid crossing wall

reduce_fan_stop_start_freq.description: If enable this setting, part cooling fan will never be stoped and will run at least at minimum speed to reduce the frequency of starting and stoping
reduce_fan_stop_start_freq.label: Keep fan always on

reduce_infill_retraction.description: Don't retract when the travel is in infill area absolutely. That means the oozing can't been seen. This can reduce times of retraction for complex model and save printing time, but make slicing and G-code generating slower
reduce_infill_retraction.label: Reduce infill retraction

required_nozzle_HRC.description: Minimum HRC of nozzle required to print the filament. Zero means no checking of nozzle's HRC.
required_nozzle_HRC.label: Required nozzle HRC

resolution.description: G-code path is genereated after simplifing the contour of model to avoid too much points and gcode lines in gcode file. Smaller value means higher resolution and more time to slice
resolution.label: Resolution

retract_before_wipe.description: The length of fast retraction before wipe, relative to retraction length
retract_before_wipe.label: Retract amount before wipe

retract_lift_above.description: If you set this to a positive value, Z lift will only take place above the specified absolute Z.
retract_lift_above.label: Only lift Z above

retract_lift_below.description: If you set this to a positive value, Z lift will only take place below the specified absolute Z.
retract_lift_below.label: Only lift Z below

retract_lift_enforce.description: Enforce Z Hop behavior. This setting is impacted by the above settings (Only lift Z above/below).
retract_lift_enforce.label: On surfaces

retract_restart_extra.description: When the retraction is compensated after the travel move, the extruder will push this additional amount of filament. This setting is rarely needed.
retract_restart_extra.label: Extra length on restart

retract_restart_extra_toolchange.description: When the retraction is compensated after changing tool, the extruder will push this additional amount of filament.
retract_restart_extra_toolchange.label: Extra length on restart

retract_when_changing_layer.description: Force a retraction when changes layer
retract_when_changing_layer.label: Retract when change layer

retraction_length.description: Some amount of material in extruder is pulled back to avoid ooze during long travel. Set zero to disable retraction
retraction_length.label: Length

retraction_minimum_travel.description: Only trigger retraction when the travel distance is longer than this threshold
retraction_minimum_travel.label: Travel distance threshold

role_based_wipe_speed.description: The wipe speed is determined by the speed of the current extrusion role.e.g. if a wipe action is executed immediately following an outer wall extrusion, the speed of the outer wall extrusion will be utilized for the wipe action.
role_based_wipe_speed.label: Role base wipe speed

scan_first_layer.description: Enable this to enable the camera on printer to check the quality of first layer
scan_first_layer.label: Scan first layer

scarf_angle_threshold.description:
This option sets the threshold angle for applying a conditional scarf joint seam.
If the maximum angle within the perimeter loop exceeds this value (indicating the absence of sharp corners), a scarf joint seam will be used. The default value is 155.
scarf_angle_threshold.label: Conditional angle threshold

scarf_joint_flow_ratio.description: This factor affects the amount of material for scarf joints.
scarf_joint_flow_ratio.label: Scarf joint flow ratio

scarf_joint_speed.description: This option sets the printing speed for scarf joints. It is recommended to print scarf joints at a slow speed (less than 100 mm/s).  It's also advisable to enable 'Extrusion rate smoothing' if the set speed varies significantly from the speed of the outer or inner walls. If the speed specified here is higher than the speed of the outer or inner walls, the printer will default to the slower of the two speeds. When specified as a percentage (e.g., 80%), the speed is calculated based on the respective outer or inner wall speed. The default value is set to 100%.
scarf_joint_speed.label: Scarf joint speed

scarf_overhang_threshold.description: This option determines the overhang threshold for the application of scarf joint seams. If the unsupported portion of the perimeter is less than this threshold, scarf joint seams will be applied. The default threshold is set at 40% of the external wall's width. Due to performance considerations, the degree of overhang is estimated.
scarf_overhang_threshold.label: Conditional overhang threshold

seam_gap.description:
In order to reduce the visibility of the seam in a closed loop extrusion, the loop is interrupted and shortened by a specified amount.
This amount can be specified in millimeters or as a percentage of the current extruder diameter. The default value for this parameter is 10%.
seam_gap.label: Seam gap

seam_position.description: The start position to print each part of outer wall
seam_position.label: Seam position

seam_slope_conditional.description: Apply scarf joints only to smooth perimeters where traditional seams do not conceal the seams at sharp corners effectively.
seam_slope_conditional.label: Conditional scarf joint

seam_slope_entire_loop.description: The scarf extends to the entire length of the wall.
seam_slope_entire_loop.label: Scarf around entire wall

seam_slope_inner_walls.description: Use scarf joint for inner walls as well.
seam_slope_inner_walls.label: Scarf joint for inner walls

seam_slope_min_length.description: Length of the scarf. Setting this parameter to zero effectively disables the scarf.
seam_slope_min_length.label: Scarf length

seam_slope_start_height.description:
Start height of the scarf.
This amount can be specified in millimeters or as a percentage of the current layer height. The default value for this parameter is 0.
seam_slope_start_height.label: Scarf start height

seam_slope_steps.description: Minimum number of segments of each scarf.
seam_slope_steps.label: Scarf steps

seam_slope_type.description: Use scarf joint to minimize seam visibility and increase seam strength.
seam_slope_type.label: Scarf joint seam (beta)

silent_mode.description: Whether the machine supports silent mode in which machine use lower acceleration to print
silent_mode.label: Supports silent mode

single_extruder_multi_material.description: Use single nozzle to print multi filament
single_extruder_multi_material.label: Single Extruder Multi Material

single_extruder_multi_material_priming.description: If enabled, all printing extruders will be primed at the front edge of the print bed at the start of the print.
single_extruder_multi_material_priming.label: Prime all printing extruders

skirt_distance.description: Distance from skirt to brim or object
skirt_distance.label: Skirt distance

skirt_height.description: How many layers of skirt. Usually only one layer
skirt_height.label: Skirt height

skirt_loops.description: Number of loops for the skirt. Zero means disabling skirt
skirt_loops.label: Skirt loops

skirt_speed.description: Speed of skirt, in mm/s. Zero means use default layer extrusion speed.
skirt_speed.label: Skirt speed

slice_closing_radius.description: Cracks smaller than 2x gap closing radius are being filled during the triangle mesh slicing. The gap closing operation may reduce the final print resolution, therefore it is advisable to keep the value reasonably low.
slice_closing_radius.label: Slice gap closing radius

slicing_mode.description: Use "Even-odd" for 3DLabPrint airplane models. Use "Close holes" to close all holes in the model.
slicing_mode.label: Slicing Mode

slow_down_for_layer_cooling.description: Enable this option to slow printing speed down to make the final layer time not shorter than the layer time threshold in "Max fan speed threshold", so that layer can be cooled for longer time. This can improve the cooling quality for needle and small details
slow_down_for_layer_cooling.label: Slow printing down for better layer cooling

slow_down_layer_time.description: The printing speed in exported gcode will be slowed down, when the estimated layer time is shorter than this value, to get better cooling for these layers
slow_down_layer_time.label: Layer time

slow_down_layers.description: The first few layers are printed slower than normal. The speed is gradually increased in a linear fashion over the specified number of layers.
slow_down_layers.label: Number of slow layers

slow_down_min_speed.description: The minimum printing speed for the filament when slow down for better layer cooling is enabled, when printing overhangs and when feature speeds are not specified explicitly.
slow_down_min_speed.label: Min print speed

slowdown_for_curled_perimeters.description: Enable this option to slow printing down in areas where potential curled perimeters may exist
slowdown_for_curled_perimeters.label: Slow down for curled perimeters

small_area_infill_flow_compensation.description: Enable flow compensation for small infill areas
small_area_infill_flow_compensation.label: Small area flow compensation (beta)

small_area_infill_flow_compensation_mode.description: Flow Compensation Model, used to adjust the flow for small infill areas. The model is expressed as a comma separated pair of values for extrusion length and flow correction factors, one per line, in the following format: "1.234,5.678"
small_area_infill_flow_compensation_mode.label: Flow Compensation Model

small_perimeter_speed.description: This separate setting will affect the speed of perimeters having radius <= small_perimeter_threshold (usually holes). If expressed as percentage (for example: 80%) it will be calculated on the outer wall speed setting above. Set to zero for auto.
small_perimeter_speed.label: Small perimeters

small_perimeter_threshold.description: This sets the threshold for small perimeter length. Default threshold is 0mm
small_perimeter_threshold.label: Small perimeters threshold

sparse_infill_acceleration.description: Acceleration of sparse infill. If the value is expressed as a percentage (e.g. 100%), it will be calculated based on the default acceleration.
sparse_infill_acceleration.label: Sparse infill

sparse_infill_density.description: Density of internal sparse infill, 100% turns all sparse infill into solid infill and internal solid infill pattern will be used
sparse_infill_density.label: Sparse infill density

sparse_infill_filament.description: Filament to print internal sparse infill.
sparse_infill_filament.label: Infill

sparse_infill_line_width.description: Line width of internal sparse infill. If expressed as a %, it will be computed over the nozzle diameter.
sparse_infill_line_width.label: Sparse infill

sparse_infill_pattern.description: Line pattern for internal sparse infill
sparse_infill_pattern.label: Sparse infill pattern

speed_limit_to_height_enable.description: Height limit speed and acceleration Enable
speed_limit_to_height_enable.label: Height limit speed and acceleration Enable

spiral_mode.description: Spiralize smooths out the z moves of the outer contour. And turns a solid model into a single walled print with solid bottom layers. The final generated model has no seam
spiral_mode.label: Spiral vase

spiral_mode_max_xy_smoothing.description: Maximum distance to move points in XY to try to achieve a smooth spiralIf expressed as a %, it will be computed over nozzle diameter
spiral_mode_max_xy_smoothing.label: Max XY Smoothing

spiral_mode_smooth.description: Smooth Spiral smoothes out X and Y moves as wellresulting in no visible seam at all, even in the XY directions on walls that are not vertical
spiral_mode_smooth.label: Smooth Spiral

staggered_inner_seams.description: This option causes the inner seams to be shifted backwards based on their depth, forming a zigzag pattern.
staggered_inner_seams.label: Staggered inner seams

start_end_points.description: The start and end points which is from cutter area to garbage can.
start_end_points.label: Start end points

support_air_filtration.description:
Enable this if printer support air filtration
G-code command: M106 P3 S(0-255)
support_air_filtration.label: Support air filtration

support_angle.description: Use this setting to rotate the support pattern on the horizontal plane.
support_angle.label: Pattern angle

support_bottom_interface_spacing.description: Spacing of bottom interface lines. Zero means solid interface
support_bottom_interface_spacing.label: Bottom interface spacing

support_bottom_z_distance.description: The z gap between the bottom support interface and object
support_bottom_z_distance.label: Bottom Z distance

support_chamber_temp_control.description:
This option is enabled if machine support controlling chamber temperature
G-code command: M141 S(0-255)
support_chamber_temp_control.label: Support control chamber temperature

support_critical_regions_only.description: Only create support for critical regions including sharp tail, cantilever, etc.
support_critical_regions_only.label: Support critical regions only

support_expansion.description: Expand (+) or shrink (-) the horizontal span of normal support
support_expansion.label: Normal Support expansion

support_filament.description: Filament to print support base and raft. "Default" means no specific filament for support and current filament is used
support_filament.label: Support/raft base

support_interface_filament.description: Filament to print support interface. "Default" means no specific filament for support interface and current filament is used
support_interface_filament.label: Support/raft interface

support_interface_loop_pattern.description: Cover the top contact layer of the supports with loops. Disabled by default.
support_interface_loop_pattern.label: Interface use loop pattern

support_interface_not_for_body.description: Avoid using support interface filament to print support base if possible.
support_interface_not_for_body.label: Avoid interface filament for base

support_interface_pattern.description: Line pattern of support interface. Default pattern for non-soluble support interface is Rectilinear, while default pattern for soluble support interface is Concentric
support_interface_pattern.label: Interface pattern

support_interface_spacing.description: Spacing of interface lines. Zero means solid interface
support_interface_spacing.label: Top interface spacing

support_line_width.description: Line width of support. If expressed as a %, it will be computed over the nozzle diameter.
support_line_width.label: Support

support_material_interface_fan_speed.description:
This fan speed is enforced during all support interfaces, to be able to weaken their bonding with a high fan speed.
Set to -1 to disable this override.
Can only be overriden by disable_fan_first_layers.
support_material_interface_fan_speed.label: Support interface fan speed

support_multi_bed_types.description: Enable this option if you want to use multiple bed types
support_multi_bed_types.label: Support multi bed types

support_object_xy_distance.description: XY separation between an object and its support
support_object_xy_distance.label: Support/object xy distance

support_on_build_plate_only.description: Don't create support on model surface, only on build plate
support_on_build_plate_only.label: On build plate only

support_remove_small_overhang.description: Remove small overhangs that possibly need no supports.
support_remove_small_overhang.label: Remove small overhangs

support_style.description:
Style and shape of the support. For normal support, projecting the supports into a regular grid will create more stable supports (default), while snug support towers will save material and reduce object scarring.
For tree support, slim and organic style will merge branches more aggressively and save a lot of material (default organic), while hybrid style will create similar structure to normal support under large flat overhangs.
support_style.label: Style

support_threshold_angle.description: Support will be generated for overhangs whose slope angle is below the threshold.
support_threshold_angle.label: Threshold angle

support_top_z_distance.description: The z gap between the top support interface and object
support_top_z_distance.label: Top Z distance

support_type.description: normal(auto) and tree(auto) is used to generate support automatically. If normal(manual) or tree(manual) is selected, only support enforcers are generated
support_type.label: Type

temperature_vitrification.description: The material softens at this temperature, so when the bed temperature is equal to or greater than it, it's highly recommended to open the front door and/or remove the upper glass to avoid cloggings.
temperature_vitrification.label: Softening temperature

template_custom_gcode.description: This G-code will be used as a custom code
template_custom_gcode.label: Custom G-code

textured_plate_temp.description: Bed temperature for layers except the initial one. Value 0 means the filament does not support to print on the Textured PEI Plate
textured_plate_temp.label: Other layers

textured_plate_temp_initial_layer.description: Bed temperature of the initial layer. Value 0 means the filament does not support to print on the Textured PEI Plate
textured_plate_temp_initial_layer.label: Initial layer

thick_bridges.description: If enabled, bridges are more reliable, can bridge longer distances, but may look worse. If disabled, bridges look better but are reliable just for shorter bridged distances.
thick_bridges.label: Thick bridges

thick_internal_bridges.description: If enabled, thick internal bridges will be used. It's usually recommended to have this feature turned on. However, consider turning it off if you are using large nozzles.
thick_internal_bridges.label: Thick internal bridges

thumbnails.description: Picture sizes to be stored into a .gcode and .sl1 / .sl1s files, in the following format: "XxY, XxY, ..."
thumbnails.label: G-code thumbnails

thumbnails_format.description: Format of G-code thumbnails: PNG for best quality, JPG for smallest size, QOI for low memory firmware
thumbnails_format.label: Format of G-code thumbnails

timelapse_type.description: If smooth or traditional mode is selected, a timelapse video will be generated for each print. After each layer is printed, a snapshot is taken with the chamber camera. All of these snapshots are composed into a timelapse video when printing completes. If smooth mode is selected, the toolhead will move to the excess chute after each layer is printed and then take a snapshot. Since the melt filament may leak from the nozzle during the process of taking a snapshot, prime tower is required for smooth mode to wipe nozzle.
timelapse_type.label: Timelapse

top_shell_layers.description: This is the number of solid layers of top shell, including the top surface layer. When the thickness calculated by this value is thinner than top shell thickness, the top shell layers will be increased
top_shell_layers.label: Top shell layers

top_shell_thickness.description: The number of top solid layers is increased when slicing if the thickness calculated by top shell layers is thinner than this value. This can avoid having too thin shell when layer height is small. 0 means that this setting is disabled and thickness of top shell is absolutely determained by top shell layers
top_shell_thickness.label: Top shell thickness

top_solid_infill_flow_ratio.description: This factor affects the amount of material for top solid infill. You can decrease it slightly to have smooth surface finish
top_solid_infill_flow_ratio.label: Top surface flow ratio

top_surface_acceleration.description: Acceleration of top surface infill. Using a lower value may improve top surface quality
top_surface_acceleration.label: Top surface

top_surface_line_width.description: Line width for top surfaces. If expressed as a %, it will be computed over the nozzle diameter.
top_surface_line_width.label: Top surface

top_surface_pattern.description: Line pattern of top surface infill
top_surface_pattern.label: Top surface pattern

top_surface_speed.description: Speed of top surface infill which is solid
top_surface_speed.label: Top surface

travel_speed.description: Speed of travel which is faster and without extrusion
travel_speed.label: Travel

tree_support_adaptive_layer_height.description: Enabling this option means the height of  tree support layer except the first will be automatically calculated
tree_support_adaptive_layer_height.label: Adaptive layer height

tree_support_angle_slow.description: The preferred angle of the branches, when they do not have to avoid the model. Use a lower angle to make them more vertical and more stable. Use a higher angle for branches to merge faster.
tree_support_angle_slow.label: Preferred Branch Angle

tree_support_auto_brim.description: Enabling this option means the width of the brim for tree support will be automatically calculated
tree_support_auto_brim.label: Auto brim width

tree_support_branch_angle.description: This setting determines the maximum overhang angle that t he branches of tree support allowed to make.If the angle is increased, the branches can be printed more horizontally, allowing them to reach farther.
tree_support_branch_angle.label: Tree support branch angle

tree_support_branch_angle_organic.description: This setting determines the maximum overhang angle that t he branches of tree support allowed to make.If the angle is increased, the branches can be printed more horizontally, allowing them to reach farther.
tree_support_branch_angle_organic.label: Tree support branch angle

tree_support_branch_diameter.description: This setting determines the initial diameter of support nodes.
tree_support_branch_diameter.label: Tree support branch diameter

tree_support_branch_diameter_angle.description: The angle of the branches' diameter as they gradually become thicker towards the bottom. An angle of 0 will cause the branches to have uniform thickness over their length. A bit of an angle can increase stability of the organic support.
tree_support_branch_diameter_angle.label: Branch Diameter Angle

tree_support_branch_diameter_double_wall.description: Branches with area larger than the area of a circle of this diameter will be printed with double walls for stability. Set this value to zero for no double walls.
tree_support_branch_diameter_double_wall.label: Branch Diameter with double walls

tree_support_branch_diameter_organic.description: This setting determines the initial diameter of support nodes.
tree_support_branch_diameter_organic.label: Tree support branch diameter

tree_support_branch_distance.description: This setting determines the distance between neighboring tree support nodes.
tree_support_branch_distance.label: Tree support branch distance

tree_support_branch_distance_organic.description: This setting determines the distance between neighboring tree support nodes.
tree_support_branch_distance_organic.label: Tree support branch distance

tree_support_brim_width.description: Distance from tree branch to the outermost brim line
tree_support_brim_width.label: Tree support brim width

tree_support_tip_diameter.description: Branch tip diameter for organic supports.
tree_support_tip_diameter.label: Tip Diameter

tree_support_top_rate.description: Adjusts the density of the support structure used to generate the tips of the branches. A higher value results in better overhangs but the supports are harder to remove, thus it is recommended to enable top support interfaces instead of a high branch density value if dense interfaces are needed.
tree_support_top_rate.label: Branch Density

tree_support_wall_count.description: This setting specify the count of walls around tree support
tree_support_wall_count.label: Tree support wall loops

tree_support_with_infill.description: This setting specifies whether to add infill inside large hollows of tree support
tree_support_with_infill.label: Tree support with infill

use_firmware_retraction.description: This experimental setting uses G10 and G11 commands to have the firmware handle the retraction. This is only supported in recent Marlin.
use_firmware_retraction.label: Use firmware retraction

use_relative_e_distances.description: Relative extrusion is recommended when using "label_objects" option.Some extruders work better with this option unckecked (absolute extrusion mode). Wipe tower is only compatible with relative mode. It is always enabled on BambuLab printers. Default is checked
use_relative_e_distances.label: Use relative E distances

wall_direction.description:
The direction which the wall loops are extruded when looking down from the top.

By default all walls are extruded in counter-clockwise, unless Reverse on odd is enabled. Set this to any option other than Auto will force the wall direction regardless of the Reverse on odd.

This option will be disabled if sprial vase mode is enabled.
wall_direction.label: Wall loop direction

wall_distribution_count.description: The number of walls, counted from the center, over which the variation needs to be spread. Lower values mean that the outer walls don't change in width
wall_distribution_count.label: Wall distribution count

wall_generator.description: Classic wall generator produces walls with constant extrusion width and for very thin areas is used gap-fill. Arachne engine produces walls with variable extrusion width
wall_generator.label: Wall generator

wall_loops.description: Number of walls of every layer
wall_loops.label: Wall loops

wall_sequence.description:
Print sequence of the internal (inner) and external (outer) walls. 

Use Inner/Outer for best overhangs. This is because the overhanging walls can adhere to a neighouring perimeter while printing. However, this option results in slightly reduced surface quality as the external perimeter is deformed by being squashed to the internal perimeter.

Use Inner/Outer/Inner for the best external surface finish and dimensional accuracy as the external wall is printed undisturbed from an internal perimeter. However, overhang performance will reduce as there is no internal perimeter to print the external wall against. This option requires a minimum of 3 walls to be effective as it prints the internal walls from the 3rd perimeter onwards first, then the external perimeter and, finally, the first internal perimeter. This option is recomended against the Outer/Inner option in most cases. 

Use Outer/Inner for the same external wall quality and dimensional accuracy benefits of Inner/Outer/Inner option. However, the z seams will appear less consistent as the first extrusion of a new layer starts on a visible surface.
wall_sequence.label: Walls printing order

wall_transition_angle.description: When to create transitions between even and odd numbers of walls. A wedge shape with an angle greater than this setting will not have transitions and no walls will be printed in the center to fill the remaining space. Reducing this setting reduces the number and length of these center walls, but may leave gaps or overextrude
wall_transition_angle.label: Wall transitioning threshold angle

wall_transition_filter_deviation.description: Prevent transitioning back and forth between one extra wall and one less. This margin extends the range of extrusion widths which follow to [Minimum wall width - margin, 2 * Minimum wall width + margin]. Increasing this margin reduces the number of transitions, which reduces the number of extrusion starts/stops and travel time. However, large extrusion width variation can lead to under- or overextrusion problems. It's expressed as a percentage over nozzle diameter
wall_transition_filter_deviation.label: Wall transitioning filter margin

wall_transition_length.description: When transitioning between different numbers of walls as the part becomes thinner, a certain amount of space is allotted to split or join the wall segments. It's expressed as a percentage over nozzle diameter
wall_transition_length.label: Wall transition length

wipe.description: Move nozzle along the last extrusion path when retracting to clean leaked material on nozzle. This can minimize blob when print new part after travel
wipe.label: Wipe while retracting

wipe_before_external_loop.description:
To minimise visibility of potential overextrusion at the start of an external perimeter when printing with Outer/Inner or Inner/Outer/Inner wall print order, the deretraction is performed slightly on the inside from the start of the external perimeter. That way any potential over extrusion is hidden from the outside surface. 

This is useful when printing with Outer/Inner or Inner/Outer/Inner wall print order as in these modes it is more likely an external perimeter is printed immediately after a deretraction move.
wipe_before_external_loop.label: Wipe before external loop

wipe_distance.description:
Discribe how long the nozzle will move along the last path when retracting. 

Depending on how long the wipe operation lasts, how fast and long the extruder/filament retraction settings are, a retraction move may be needed to retract the remaining filament. 

Setting a value in the retract amount before wipe setting below will perform any excess retraction before the wipe, else it will be performed after.
wipe_distance.label: Wipe Distance

wipe_on_loops.description: To minimize the visibility of the seam in a closed loop extrusion, a small inward movement is executed before the extruder leaves the loop.
wipe_on_loops.label: Wipe on loops

wipe_speed.description: The wipe speed is determined by the speed setting specified in this configuration.If the value is expressed as a percentage (e.g. 80%), it will be calculated based on the travel speed setting above.The default value for this parameter is 80%
wipe_speed.label: Wipe speed

wipe_tower_bridging.description: Maximal distance between supports on sparse infill sections.
wipe_tower_bridging.label: Maximal bridging distance

wipe_tower_cone_angle.description: Angle at the apex of the cone that is used to stabilize the wipe tower. Larger angle means wider base.
wipe_tower_cone_angle.label: Stabilization cone apex angle

wipe_tower_extra_spacing.description: Spacing of purge lines on the wipe tower.
wipe_tower_extra_spacing.label: Wipe tower purge lines spacing

wipe_tower_extruder.description: The extruder to use when printing perimeter of the wipe tower. Set to 0 to use the one that is available (non-soluble would be preferred).
wipe_tower_extruder.label: Wipe tower extruder

wipe_tower_no_sparse_layers.description: If enabled, the wipe tower will not be printed on layers with no toolchanges. On layers with a toolchange, extruder will travel downward to print the wipe tower. User is responsible for ensuring there is no collision with the print.
wipe_tower_no_sparse_layers.label: No sparse layers (EXPERIMENTAL)

wipe_tower_rotation_angle.description: Wipe tower rotation angle with respect to x-axis.
wipe_tower_rotation_angle.label: Wipe tower rotation angle

wiping_volumes_extruders.description: This vector saves required volumes to change from/to each tool used on the wipe tower. These values are used to simplify creation of the full purging volumes below.
wiping_volumes_extruders.label: Purging volumes - load/unload volumes

xy_contour_compensation.description: Contour of object will be grown or shrunk in XY plane by the configured value. Positive value makes contour bigger. Negative value makes contour smaller. This function is used to adjust size slightly when the object has assembling issue
xy_contour_compensation.label: X-Y contour compensation

xy_hole_compensation.description: Holes of object will be grown or shrunk in XY plane by the configured value. Positive value makes holes bigger. Negative value makes holes smaller. This function is used to adjust size slightly when the object has assembling issue
xy_hole_compensation.label: X-Y hole compensation

z_hop.description: Whenever the retraction is done, the nozzle is lifted a little to create clearance between nozzle and the print. It prevents nozzle from hitting the print when travel move. Using spiral line to lift z can prevent stringing
z_hop.label: Z hop when retract

z_offset.description: This value will be added (or subtracted) from all the Z coordinates in the output G-code. It is used to compensate for bad Z endstop position: for example, if your endstop zero actually leaves the nozzle 0.3mm far from the print bed, set this to -0.3 (or fix your endstop).
z_offset.label: Z offset
